cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.NE 

The paper deals with the application of deep learning techniques for cancer metastasis detection in Whole-slide Images (WSIs). This falls under the domain of computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed method involves the use of a neural conditional random field (NCRF) which is a probabilistic graphical model, indicating the possibility of the paper being categorized under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the use of a fully connected CRF component in the proposed method suggests the possibility of the paper being categorized under neural networks (cs.NE).
